      <thead><tr><th>Code</th><th>Meaning</th><th>Common cause</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>OE</td><td>Drain fault</td><td>Pump filter (DIY first), pump motor</td></tr>
        <tr><td>IE</td><td>Inlet fault</td><td>Water supply, hose, valve</td></tr>
        <tr><td>UE</td><td>Unbalanced</td><td>Load redistribution; suspension on persistent</td></tr>
        <tr><td>LE</td><td>Motor lock / interlock</td><td>Door interlock or motor stall</td></tr>
        <tr><td>PE</td><td>Pressure sensor</td><td>Pressure switch or hose to switch</td></tr>
        <tr><td>CE</td><td>Motor communication</td><td>Control board to motor harness or board</td></tr>
        <tr><td>FE</td><td>Overflow</td><td>Inlet valve stuck open</td></tr>
        <tr><td>tE</td><td>Temperature sensor</td><td>Thermistor</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>LG linear-drive direct-drive units have a built-in diagnostic mode (button-press sequence on power-up). We use it on every LG service call. Cross-link: <a href="/brands/lg-washer-repair/">LG washer repair</a>.</p>
